Description: Fix CVE-2025-15649 - handle zero/invalid DOS datetime in IO::Uncompress::Unzip
 IO::Uncompress::Unzip::_dosToUnixTime did not handle zero or out-of-range
 DOS datetime fields in zip headers. Upstream versions that call
 Time::Local::timelocal can die with an uncaught exception (CWE-248).
 Bullseye's bundled copy (Unzip 2.093) still uses POSIX::mktime, which
 normalizes rather than dies, but the same defensive contract from the
 upstream fix still applies: return 0 for an unpopulated (zero) datetime
 and reject out-of-range decoded fields instead of silently normalizing
 them into a different timestamp.
 .
 This bullseye backport:
   * returns 0 immediately when $dt is zero;
   * validates the decoded DOS datetime with Time::Local before using
     the existing POSIX::mktime conversion, so malformed fields are
     rejected instead of being normalized.
 .
 The two binary test fixtures from the upstream commit
 (t/files/time-invalid.zip and t/files/time-zero.zip) are intentionally
 omitted: tests are not shipped in the runtime Debian binary package,
 and GNU patch -p1 (used by quilt fold) does not support git binary
 hunks. The runtime source fix is unaffected.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/fd28c1d2374eee9811f6d0c5bddc0957abdf1da8
Author: pmqs <pmqs@cpan.org>
Last-Update: 2026-07-17
---
--- a/cpan/IO-Compress/lib/IO/Uncompress/Unzip.pm
+++ b/cpan/IO-Compress/lib/IO/Uncompress/Unzip.pm
@@ -771,6 +771,9 @@
 {
 	my $dt = shift;
 
+    # some zip files don't populate the datetime field at all
+    return 0 if ! $dt;
+
 	my $year = ( ( $dt >> 25 ) & 0x7f ) + 80;
 	my $mon  = ( ( $dt >> 21 ) & 0x0f ) - 1;
 	my $mday = ( ( $dt >> 16 ) & 0x1f );
@@ -780,6 +783,13 @@
 	my $sec  = ( ( $dt << 1 ) & 0x3e );
 
 
+    # mktime normalizes invalid fields, so validate them first.
+    require Time::Local;
+    return 0 if ! eval {
+        Time::Local::timelocal( $sec, $min, $hour, $mday, $mon, $year );
+        1;
+    };
+
     use POSIX 'mktime';
 
     my $time_t = mktime( $sec, $min, $hour, $mday, $mon, $year, 0, 0, -1 );
From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] CVE-2026-48961 not-affected documentation for perl 5.32.1 (bullseye)

---
 ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md | 39 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 39 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md

diff --git a/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md b/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..b1c2d3e
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md
@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@
+# Security False-Positive Analysis — CVE-2026-48961 (perl, Debian bullseye)
+
+**CVE-2026-48961** — *not-affected*
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| CVE | CVE-2026-48961 |
+| Package | `perl` (bundled `cpan/IO-Compress/bin/zipdetails`) |
+| Distribution | Debian 11 (bullseye) |
+| Shipped version | `5.32.1-4+deb11u5` (IO::Uncompress::Unzip 2.093 / old zipdetails) |
+| Verdict | **not-affected** — `unpackValueQ` typo not present |
+| Affected range | IO::Compress **2.207 before 2.220** (zipdetails 4.000–4.005) |
+| Introduced | https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/ddfe67584a228877e5d28840da75ff32e435a5e3 (v2.207) |
+| CWE | CWE-755 |
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+CVE-2026-48961: `zipdetails` calls misspelled `unpackValueQ` (should be
+`unpackValue_Q`) when decoding an 8-byte UID/GID in Info-ZIP ux (0x7875).
+
+## Why bullseye perl is not affected
+
+Bundled IO::Compress is **2.093-era** / pre-2.207 zipdetails.
+`decodeLitteEndian()` only handles 4-byte values (`die "unsupported"` otherwise)
+and never calls `unpackValueQ`. Debian already marks bullseye
+`libio-compress-perl` **not-affected** ("Vulnerable code introduced later").
+
+## Verdict
+
+**No code patch required.** See `patches/CVE-2026-48961/README.md`.
+
+## References
+
+- https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-48961
+- https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48961
+- https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/33c89d03d6e746ed2ead4f2f6570d47864c61bc7
+<!-- SECURITY-RELEASE-ANCHOR -->
Description: CVE-2026-8376 - heap buffer overflow in Perl_study_chunk on 32-bit builds
 .
 A heap buffer overflow in Perl_study_chunk (regcomp.c, regcomp_study.c
 upstream) affecting 32-bit builds when compiling regular expressions
 containing a repeated fixed string. The byte calculation mincount * l
 could overflow SSize_t, leading to an undersized SvGROW allocation and an
 out-of-bounds write during the subsequent copy. Add an explicit overflow
 check and fail with "Regexp out of space" instead.
 .
 Note: the upstream commit also un-TODOs a regression test in
 t/re/pat_psycho.t (sec #147). That test block does not exist in 5.32.1,
 so the test-side hunk is skipped here.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/Perl/perl5/commit/5e7f119eb2bb1181be908701f22bf7068e722f1c
