Description: CVE-2026-42497 - Validate hardlink linkname in SECURE MODE
 Archive::Tar before 3.08 forwards tar header linkname to link() without
 rejecting absolute paths or '..' traversal segments. An attacker-crafted
 archive can create a hardlink to a victim file outside the extract
 directory; the post-extraction chmod/chown/utime then mutates the victim
 inode. This patch validates hardlink linkname against absolute paths and
 parent-directory traversal in SECURE MODE.
