Description: CVE-2026-57432 - Fix SSize_t overflow in pack()/unpack() template structure size calculation
 Avoid ssize_t overflow when calculating the size of a structure in
 S_measure_struct (pp_pack.c). A crafted pack/unpack template could
 cause the accumulated structure size to overflow SSize_t, leading to
 memory corruption. Adds an explicit overflow check that croaks with
 "Pack template structure size is too large" instead of silently
 wrapping, plus additional overflow-safety hardening for the B/b and
 H/h format-code rounding-division calculations.
 .
 This patch folds two upstream commits:
  * 5f7eb6bbbe0510964e3fb1d6bb691e5445913e55 - detect the len*size and
    total+len*size overflow and croak with a new diagnostic (also adds the
    "Pack template structure size is too large" entry to perldiag.pod).
  * 40754edc72dd3e513d758153c0e2f0215897740e - avoid additional potential
    overflows in the 'B'/'b' and 'H'/'h' size rounding.
 .
 Adaptation for Perl 5.32.1: use Perl_croak(aTHX_ ...) to match the
 surrounding style in this version's pp_pack.c (upstream uses croak()).
Origin: upstream, commit:5f7eb6bbbe0510964e3fb1d6bb691e5445913e55, commit:40754edc72dd3e513d758153c0e2f0215897740e
Author: Paul "LeoNerd" Evans <leonerd@leonerd.org.uk>
Last-Update: 2026-07-17
---
--- a/pp_pack.c
+++ b/pp_pack.c
@@ -512,12 +512,12 @@
 		break;
 	    case 'B':
 	    case 'b':
-		len = (len + 7)/8;
+		len = (len / 8) + !!(len % 8);
 		size = 1;
 		break;
 	    case 'H':
 	    case 'h':
-		len = (len + 1)/2;
+		len = (len / 2) + !!(len % 2);
 		size = 1;
 		break;
 
@@ -527,6 +527,10 @@
 		break;
 	    }
 	}
+	if ((size > 0) &&
+		((len > SSize_t_MAX / size) ||         /* detect overflow of len * size */
+		 (len * size > SSize_t_MAX - total)))  /* detect overflow of total + len * size */
+		Perl_croak(aTHX_ "Pack template structure size is too large");
 	total += len * size;
     }
     return total;
